00:00:03.660 --> 00:00:08.550
Unmanned aerial vehicles or UAVs have
undoubtedly established themselves

00:00:08.550 --> 00:00:12.150
as an effective force multiplier in
the theater of military operations.

00:00:12.780 --> 00:00:15.630
UAVs have been successfully
used for surveillance,

00:00:15.930 --> 00:00:18.060
reconnaissance, and combat missions.

00:00:18.975 --> 00:00:21.975
In recent years, there has been
an increased interest in drone

00:00:21.975 --> 00:00:26.115
swarms or multiple drones working
together, however, the potential of

00:00:26.115 --> 00:00:28.035
such technology is yet to be seen.

00:00:28.995 --> 00:00:33.255
But what exactly are drone swarms and why
are they making headlines all of a sudden?

00:00:33.975 --> 00:00:34.785
Let's find out.

00:00:34.785 --> 00:00:35.235
Together.

00:00:35.235 --> 00:00:40.635
In this episode of Explained in
May, 2021, the Israeli Defense

00:00:40.635 --> 00:00:44.565
Forces became the first military
to employ a drone swarm in combat.

00:00:45.480 --> 00:00:49.110
Little is known about the event except
that Israel used the swarm attack

00:00:49.110 --> 00:00:52.740
to strike dozens of targets together
with other missiles and munitions.

00:00:53.610 --> 00:00:58.440
Most media outlets reported this as an
attack with multiple drones at once, but

00:00:58.440 --> 00:01:02.760
military experts believed that this was
a true drone swarm attack, meaning that

00:01:02.760 --> 00:01:05.745
the drones communicated and collaborated
in making collective decisions.

00:01:07.125 --> 00:01:09.945
Swarming as a concept is not new.

00:01:10.575 --> 00:01:12.285
Swarms can be found in nature.

00:01:12.915 --> 00:01:16.965
Think of schools of fish, flocks
of birds, or swarms of insects.

00:01:17.565 --> 00:01:21.195
With that said, swarming is not
limited to natural phenomena.

00:01:21.585 --> 00:01:25.575
That is also a long established military
tactic that occurs when several units

00:01:25.575 --> 00:01:28.965
come together to attack a target
from multiple sides in a purposely

00:01:28.965 --> 00:01:30.855
structured and highly coordinated way.

00:01:31.785 --> 00:01:35.565
This type of swarming has occurred
throughout military history from horse

00:01:35.565 --> 00:01:40.065
archers in the fourth century to swarm
like cyber attacks in the 21st century,

00:01:40.425 --> 00:01:42.405
and it is now being applied to drones.

00:01:43.755 --> 00:01:46.875
Drone swarms represent a group
of unmanned aircraft systems

00:01:46.875 --> 00:01:49.905
that operate collaboratively to
achieve common objectives with

00:01:49.905 --> 00:01:52.185
an operator on her in the loop.

00:01:52.665 --> 00:01:55.755
Coordination and reactivity
are crucial in drone swarms.

00:01:56.085 --> 00:01:59.595
They actually represent the key
difference between a real drone swarm

00:01:59.745 --> 00:02:01.515
and the employment of mass drones.

00:02:02.415 --> 00:02:06.075
The latter occurs when a number of drones
are deployed against a single threat,

00:02:06.465 --> 00:02:08.655
mainly to overwhelm the enemy's defenses.

00:02:09.525 --> 00:02:13.245
However, each platform is usually
separately controlled and there

00:02:13.245 --> 00:02:16.155
is no link or coordination
between the drones themselves.

00:02:16.995 --> 00:02:21.135
Drones operating in a swarm, however,
are interlinked and are in constant

00:02:21.135 --> 00:02:22.575
communication with each other.

00:02:23.205 --> 00:02:26.625
The quantity of drones in a swarm
can range from a few hundred to

00:02:26.625 --> 00:02:31.665
billions and can vary in size and
type by constantly sharing sensor

00:02:31.665 --> 00:02:32.925
information among each other.

00:02:33.285 --> 00:02:36.525
They are programmed to make AI
driven collective decisions in

00:02:36.525 --> 00:02:38.085
order to achieve the set goal.

00:02:38.985 --> 00:02:39.525
This link.

00:02:39.855 --> 00:02:43.965
Along with the AI software are vital
in creating the hive mind that sets

00:02:43.965 --> 00:02:48.795
drone swarms apart and allows it to
function effectively in the hive mind.

00:02:48.885 --> 00:02:52.815
Certain drones can use their sensors
to locate and track targets sharing

00:02:52.815 --> 00:02:56.535
this information with the rest of
the swarm, while others can perform

00:02:56.535 --> 00:03:00.645
electronic warfare tasks and the
rest can engage hostile forces.

00:03:01.275 --> 00:03:05.565
This way the swarm can react dynamically
to changes in the battle space by

00:03:05.565 --> 00:03:07.485
performing these complex maneuvers.

00:03:08.340 --> 00:03:12.269
This is what makes drone swarms
extremely dangerous and thus desirable

00:03:12.269 --> 00:03:13.950
by every military on the planet.

00:03:15.420 --> 00:03:19.500
We mentioned that Israel's military
already deployed drone swarm attacks, but

00:03:19.500 --> 00:03:24.030
other countries have similar capabilities
too, including the French Iist Project,

00:03:24.630 --> 00:03:29.609
the UAE, and South African and Raven,
the Russian Lightning, the Spanish

00:03:29.609 --> 00:03:32.429
rappers, and the UK's Blue Bear Swarm.

00:03:33.345 --> 00:03:36.644
The Indian Army also showed off
their drone swarm capability

00:03:36.644 --> 00:03:40.545
during a live demonstration for
India's Army Day in early 2021.

00:03:41.505 --> 00:03:45.015
Needless to say, the US and
China also have a number of swarm

00:03:45.015 --> 00:03:46.545
programs in place for years.

00:03:46.545 --> 00:03:51.795
Now, while countering large number of
drones is proving very difficult already

00:03:51.795 --> 00:03:56.685
countering swarms, raises the bar even
further, although some organizations.

00:03:57.105 --> 00:04:01.665
Including the UN are beginning to
classify drone swarms as weapons of mass

00:04:01.665 --> 00:04:05.955
destruction Due to the deadly combination
of mass harm and lack of human control,

00:04:06.375 --> 00:04:08.505
drone swarms are proliferating rapidly.

00:04:09.435 --> 00:04:11.655
What happens next remains to be seen.

00:04:12.555 --> 00:04:16.185
Are drone swarms really the future of
unmanned warfare, or should they be

00:04:16.185 --> 00:04:18.405
classified as weapons of mass destruction?

